<strong>BIBLIOGRAPHY ENTRY</strong>
<br><br>
Add a bibliography at the end of your essay citing all relevant sources used in your research, regardless of whether they are explicitly mentioned in your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Editor&#8217;s surname, given name, ed. <em>Title of Book</em>. Place of publication: Publisher, year of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Editor&39;s name">Smith, Amy</span>, ed. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Book">Invertebrate Taxonomy: A Guide to Big Names</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">Wellington</span>: 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Kowhai Press</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="year of publication">2056</span>.
</blockquote>
